                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War/9–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>, United
                        States Political Adviser on the Staff of the Supreme Allied Commander,
                        Mediterranean Theater</hi> (<persName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-07T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 7, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>312. My 295, September 4, midnight. General Wilson has now sent instructions to
                    Lieutenant Colonel Barnes that there is no objection to his meeting Von Lanz but
                    he is not to discuss terms of surrender. Purpose of such a meeting would be to
                    arrange evacuation of a senior German officer to AFHQ to receive surrender
                    terms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
